Write a C program to convert a given temperature from Fahrenheit (F) to Celsius (C).
Include the necessary prompts for user input and ensure the program displays the converted temperature in a formatted output.

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    float fahrenheit, celsius;
    printf("Enter temperature in Fahrenheit: ");
    scanf("%f", &fahrenheit);
    celsius = (fahrenheit - 32) * 5 / 9;
    printf("Temperature in Celsius: %.2f\n", celsius);
    return 0;
}
*****************************************************************************************************************
OUTPUT:
Enter temperature in Fahrenheit: 45
Temperature in Celsius: 7.22
*****************************************************************************************************************
